.TH "NAVIGATIONCURRENTENTRYCHANGEEVENT" "3JS" "December 8, 2025" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
NavigationCurrentEntryChangeEvent \- NavigationCurrentEntryChangeEvent
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]NavigationCurrentEntryChangeEvent\f[B]\f[R] interface of
the Navigation API is the event object for the
\f[CR]currententrychange\f[R] event, which fires when the
\f[CR]Navigation.currentEntry\f[R] has changed.
.PP
This event will fire for same\-document navigations (e.g.,
\f[CR]back()\f[R] or \f[CR]traverseTo()\f[R]), replacements (i.e., a
\f[CR]navigate()\f[R] call with \f[CR]history\f[R] set to
\f[CR]replace\f[R]), or other calls that change the entry\(cqs state
(e.g., \f[CR]updateCurrentEntry()\f[R], or the History API\(cqs
\f[CR]History.replaceState()\f[R]).
.PP
This event fires after the navigation is committed, meaning that the
visible URL has changed and the \f[CR]NavigationHistoryEntry\f[R] update
has occurred.
It is useful for migrating from usage of older API features like the
\f[CR]hashchange\f[R] or \f[CR]popstate\f[R] events.
.SH CONSTRUCTOR
.TP
\f[B]NavigationCurrentEntryChangeEvent()\f[R]
Creates a new \f[CR]NavigationCurrentEntryChangeEvent\f[R] object
instance.
.SH INSTANCE PROPERTIES
\f[I]Inherits properties from its parent, \f[CI]Event\f[I].\f[R]
.TP
\f[B]from\f[R] \f[I](read\-only)\f[R]
Returns the \f[CR]NavigationHistoryEntry\f[R] that was navigated from.
.TP
\f[B]navigationType\f[R] \f[I](read\-only)\f[R]
Returns the type of the navigation that resulted in the change.
.SH EXAMPLES
Navigation data reporting:
.IP
.EX
navigation.addEventListener(\(dqcurrententrychange\(dq, () \f[B]=>\f[R] {
  \f[B]const\f[R] data = navigation.currentEntry.getState();
  submitAnalyticsData(data.analytics);
});
.EE
.PP
Setting up a per\-entry event:
.IP
.EX
navigation.addEventListener(\(dqcurrententrychange\(dq, () \f[B]=>\f[R] {
  navigation.currentEntry.addEventListener(\(dqdispose\(dq, genericDisposeHandler);
});
.EE
